                            <comment id="12989484" author="kelvin" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 01:15:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;caught by distributed testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989485" author="kelvin" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 01:16:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;do not re-use digest message object.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989490" author="kelvin" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 01:31:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;future reference: please test w/ RF=3, which is a more interesting case for CL.ALL.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989649" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 14:33:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for catching that, Kelvin!  committed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(FWIW this is a regression from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1959&quot; title=&quot;java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException while executing repair on a freshly added node (0.7.0)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1959&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1959&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12989657" author="hudson" created="Wed, 2 Feb 2011 14:52:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.7 #234 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/234/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.7/234/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    remove digestMessage reuse to fix regression from #1959&lt;br/&gt;
patch by Kelvin Kakugawa; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2094&quot; title=&quot;fix regression in CL.ALL read&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2094&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2094&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
